Name: City TEAM Recovery Program
Description: One-year residential drug recovery program
Notes: Call ahead if you can; apply clean & sober M-F 9-10am. Stay up to 1 yr.

Name: A Woman's Place
Address: 1049 HOWARD (bet. 6th & 7th Sts; enter on Russ St.)
Description: 5 beds for women in crisis (rape or domestic violence); stay up to 7 days. 16 shelter beds; stay varies. 16 beds in supportive housing (5 for HIV+ women); stay up to 18 months. 8-bed substance abuse program for any woman 18+; stay 1-4 months.
Hours: Drop in 12pm-4pm for referrals & case management
Notes: Call for interview. Phone line open 24 hours a day.

Name: CHANGES: Mission Neighborhood R.C.
Description: For a 90-day bed in 1 of 8 shelters, line up by 7am. For a 1-night bed, apply during the hours listed.
Notes: You’ll be photographed & your finger image will be scanned into a computer for future use. It won’t be saved without your consent. They’ll ask for your Social Security number, but you don’t have to give it. You’ll get a reservation for a bed or mat if one is available. If no bed is available you can wait there during open hours until a bed opens up. You can request a ride to the shelter if elderly or disabled. At the shelter your finger image will be scanned again but not saved. English, Spanish.

Description: For a 90-day bed in 1 of 8 shelters, line up by 7am. For a 1-night bed, apply during the hours listed.
Notes: You’ll be photographed & your finger image will be scanned into a computer for future use. It won’t be saved without your consent. They’ll ask for your Social Security number, but you don’t have to give it. You’ll get a reservation for a bed or mat if one is available. Description: 1-night bed and 24 hour drop-in showers and support services available. Doctors on site.
Hours: Daily 10am (to reserve a place on the priority list for a 1-night bed, assignable at 6:30pm) or 5-9pm (to apply for a 1-night bed). The MSC is also a 24-hr drop-in center with showers & supportive services available, where you can wait for a bed if there is space. Doctors on site: M 1:30-4pm, 6-8pm (dental); Tu 2-4pm, 6-8pm; W 8am-noon, 7:30-9pm (foot clinic 1st & 3rd W); Th 2-5pm, 6-8pm; F 8am-noon.
Notes: You’ll be photographed & your finger image will be scanned into a computer for future use. It won’t be saved without your consent. At the shelter your finger image will be scanned again but not saved. English, Spanish.

Name: Asian Women’s Shelter
Description: For battered women (with or without children). Stay up to 12 wks. Priority to women or transgendered people &their children, with limited resources, who don’t speak English.
Phone: (415) 751-0880 (24 hrs) or 877-751-0880 (24 hrs & toll free) for intake interview. 5pm-9am, calls are answered by Woman, Inc. for crisis counseling.
Hours: New guests M-F only, except in emergencies.
Notes: Kitchen & basic food provided for cooking; referrals, counseling & clothing available. Staff speaks Arabic, Cantonese, English, Hindi, Hmong, Indonesian, Japanese, Javanese, Laotian, Mandarin, Mien, Punjabi, Russian, Spanish, Taiwanese, Thai, Urdu, & Vietnamese; other languages by phone interpreter

Name: La Casa de las Madres
Address: OFFICE: 1663 MISSION, SUITE 225 (bet. So. Van Ness & 13 St)
Description:
For battered women (with or without children). Program includes counseling, house meetings, 3 meals daily, & chores. Stay up to 8
weeks. For non-residents: support groups, individual counseling, legal aid with restraining orders.
Phone: Crisis line: 877-503-1850. Teen crisis line: 877-923-0700 (counseling & referrals only). All numbers are 24 hrs & toll free. Call 877-503-1850 anytime for shelter

Name: Rosalie House
Description: For battered women (with or without children). Adults $0-1 per week (kids free); stay up to 12 weeks. Guests can’t use drugs or alcohol. Program includes counseling, house meetings & chores. Kitchen & food available.

Name: Connecting Point
Description: Not a shelter itself, but offers placement in shelters for 1- or 2-parent families, expectant couples & pregnant women (with proof) & sometimes household members. Samesex couples accepted. Wait 5-6 months for shelter placement, with case management while waiting.
Phone: Call toll free 855-234-2667 (M-F 9am-noon; MWF 1-5pm, Tu 3-5pm, Th 2-5pm).
Notes: Call for intake interview. If you get an answering machine, leave your name & phone number. If you don’t have a return number, call until you get through. Ask about possible financial help for families facing eviction or move-in costs. Cantonese, English, French, Spanish.

Name: Missionaries of Charity
Description: Women with or without kids (one girl child; or one boy under 4 years); pregnant women (with proof) may stay up to one month after childbirth; others stay up to one month.
Notes: Be clean & sober, with proof of negative TB & HIV status, & able to live a communal life. Call for appointment for personal interview. 2 meals daily. Leave the house by 9am. Curfew 5pm. No new shelter guests accepted Th.

Name: Diamond Youth Shelter
Description: Shelter for Youths. Dinner, breakfast, showers, counseling & referrals. Length of stay varies. Guardians contacted within 72 hours.
Hours: Youths 12-17 call; or show up M-F 6:30pm- 7:30am, Sa-Sun 4pm-7:30am.

Name: Diamond Youth Shelter Drop-In Center
Description: Drop-In Clinic for youths. Showers, lockers, food, clothing, case management, education & counseling. English, Spanish.

Name: Huckleberry House
Description: Shelter for Youths. 3 meals daily for shelter guests; access to medical services, case management, and individual & family therapy. English, Spanish.
Notes: Youths 11-17 who are not on probation, call if you can or show up to be assessed for short-term housing. If accepted, they’ll contact your guardians within 24 hrs.

Name: Lark Inn
Description: Shelter fo Youths 18-24.  Length of stay varies; maximum 4 months. 3 meals daily for long-term shelter guests. Job readiness training, remedial education, GED & college-entry prep available. Up to 21 nights per year of emergency shelter; show up at 9:45pm each night for lottery. English, Spanish.
Notes:
Come in or call any time (24 hrs) to get on waiting list for a bed (40 beds nightly).  Case management required. Curfew 9:45pm. Leave
by 8:30am.

Name: San Francisco General Hospital
Description: Urgent and Primary Care HIV, and Pregnancy testing, Family Planning, Women's Health, Mental Health, and Prenatal Care. For SF residents. $0-full bill. Call for appt.
Notes: Patient Advocates call (415) 206-5176. Cantonese, English, Mandarin, Russian, Spanish, and Vietnamese. Other languages available.

Photo ID, proof of income, & proof of current address required for both services. English, Cantonese, Mandarin, Spanish, Tagalog, Vietnamese.

Name: Temple United Methodist Church
Description: weekly food pantry (Wednesday). Call for Appointment
Notes: Call 211 to apply for a weekly appt to pick up food Wed 4-7pm. Must live in zip code 94112, 94116, 94127, or 94132. Approved clients must bring registration card & photo ID with current address to pick up food.

Name: Mary Elizabeth Inn
Description: weekly food pantry (Wednesday). Women only.
Notes: line up 9am Wed; food given out 9-10am; bring a bag.

Name: Project Open Hand
Description: food pantry for people with HIV/AIDS or breast cancer
Notes: People with symptomatic HIV or AIDS or breast cancer: call M-Sa 9am-4pm for interview appt. If accepted, pick up food Tues 9am-4pm, Wed-Sat 11am-4pm. Proof of diagnosis & SF residency & photo ID required.

Name: S.F. Rescue Mission
Description: sign up to get food one Thursday a month
Notes: Sign up Wed 12-12:30pm to get food one Thurs a month 12-12:30pm. Must live in 94102 zip code. Photo ID & proof of address required

Name: Salvation Army Chinatown
Description: weekly food pantry (Friday)
Notes:
Call MWF 9am-4pm for interview appt. If accepted, get food Fri 3pm. If not
signed up, come Fri 2:30pm to see if there’s extra food. Must live in 94108, 94109, 94111, 94123, 94129, 94130, 94133, or 94158 zip code. English, Cantonese, Mandarin.

Name: Salvation Army Kroc Center
Description: weekly food pantry (Friday)
Notes: Register Friday 7:30am to get food the following Friday. Must live in 94102, 94103, 94115, 94117, 94118, or 94121 zip code. ID required.

Name: Salvation Army South of Market
Description: weekly food pantry (Friday)
Notes: Food given out Fri 8:30am (line up early to get a number). You must live in 94104 or 94105 zip code. ID required. English, Cantonese, & Mandarin.

Name: Youth With A Mission
Description: weekly food pantry (Thursday)
Notes: Line up Thur 11am; food given out. Must live in 94102 zip code. ID required

Name: Bethel AME Church
Description: provides weekly boxes of food for six months. must sign up
Notes: Apply 8am-noon Fri, Oct 12 for a randomly-assigned appt (not first-come-firstserved) to get food weekly for six months. ID required. Bring a bag

Name: Booker T. Washington Community Svce Ctr.
Description: weekly food pantry (Thursday)
Notes: Call Wed 9am-noon for appt to get food Thur 11:30am-1pm. Produce, canned & dry goods. Photo ID required.

Name: First Friendship Institutional Baptist Church
Description: weekly food pantry (Friday)
Notes: Sign up 9am Friday for appt to pick up food Fri morning. You must live in 94115 or 94117 zip code. Bring a bag. Photo ID required.

Name: Jones Memorial United Methodist Church
Description: weekly food pantry
Notes: Sign up 10:30-11:30am Sat for weekly appt to pick up food. Must live in 94102, 94109 or 94115 zip code. ID & proof of current address required. Bring a bag.

Name: Korean American Senior Service
Description: weekly food pantry (Friday)
Notes: ID required

Name: Macedonia Missionary Baptist Church
Description: weekly food pantry (Wednesday)
Notes: Must live in 94102, 94109, or 94115 zip code. ID required

Name: St. Andrew Missionary Baptist Church
Description: weekly food pantry (wednesday). sign up to get food for the the next 90 days
Notes: Don’t line up before 8am. Sign up Wed Jan 2, 8:15am for appt to get food Wed morning for next 90 days. Those not signed up can come Wed 10:15am to see if there’s extra food. No ID required, just a smile.

Name: Treasure Island Homeless Development Initiative
Address: 850 AVENUE I ON TREASURE ISLAND (at 9th St, in the Shipshape Building).
Description: weekly food pantry (Tuesday)
Notes: For Treasure Island residents only. ID & lease required.

Name: Supplemental Food Program
Description: Citywide program. Call 211 for nearest location to get one 35lb box of dry & canned goods per month. For SF residents age 60+ & non-WIC families with children under 6. Must provide proof of age & income.

Name: WIC
Description: WIC provides food vouchers, info & support for breastfeeding, & nutritional counseling. You can take vouchers to some grocery stores for fruits & vegetables, whole grains, beans (or peanut butter), cereal, juice, eggs, milk, cheese, iron-fortified infant formula & baby food for infants.
Notes: Women who are pregnant of have children under 5 years, call for referral to sign up in one of 6 locations. Bring proof of income, address, & verification of pregnancy.

Name: Glide Memorial Church
Description: Dinning room that serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner Monday-Friday. Limited Food Service Saturday and Sunday.
Notes: Breakfast: Every day from 8am until tickets run out; Seniors (over age 60) 7:30am. Lunch: Every day from noon until tickets run out; bag meal (2 sandwiches+) given out after lunch Sat & Sun. Dinner: Monday-Friday from 4pm until tickets run out.

Name: St. Anthony Foundation
Description: Dinning room that serves lunch everyday. All entrees served with fruit, vegetables, bread, beverage, and dessert!
Notes: Full-course meal. Families & folks age 60+ or unable to carry a tray: 10-11:30am. All others: 11:30am-1:30pm. When you arrive you will be given a number for a meal. You may be asked to go wait at 240 Golden Gate until your number is called.

Name: All Saints' Episcopal Church
Description: Dinning room serving Saturday Brunch
Notes: Meat; potatoes or pasta or rice; vegetables, salad, pastry, coffee & bread

Name: City Team Ministries
Description: A hot meal served 5 days a week
Hours: Tues-Fri 5:45pm (for church group)/ 6pm for meal, Sat 1pm-3pm
Notes: Dinner: Tues-Fri arrive 5:45pm for 6pm church group (optional) & dinner. Those who come to church group are fed first. A hot meal. Clothes & foot care available at Sat lunch. Medical clinic 2nd & 4th Sat of each month.

Name: Curry Senior Center
Description: Dining room serving seniors. Breakfast and lunch served everyday
Notes: For those age 60 & over with ID. $2 suggested donation; no one turned away for lack of funds. Sign up 8am for lunch.

Name: Curry Without Worry
Address: HYDE & FULTON (by the statue of Bolívar)
Description: A hot meal served once a week (Tuesdays) for dinner.
Notes: Vegan! Curried vegetables, 9-bean soup, puris, rice, & chutney.

Name: Food Not Bombs (UN PLAZA)
Description: A hot meal served twice a week for dinner.
Notes: Vegan! soup &/or entree;bread (may have animal products); often salad. Bring your own bowl. Meal times vary: often late or cancelled.

Name: Food Not Bombs (16TH & MISSION)
Description: A hot meal served twice a week for dinner.
Notes: Vegan! soup &/or entree;bread (may have animal products); often salad. Bring your own bowl. Meal times vary: often late or cancelled.

Name: Food Not Bombs (HAIGHT & STANYAN)
Description: A hot meal served once a week for dinner.
Notes: Vegan! soup &/or entree;bread (may have animal products); often salad. Bring your own bowl. Meal times vary: often late or cancelled.

Name: Fraternié Notre Dame (Turk)
Description: A hot meal.

Name: Fraternitè Notre Dame (UN Plaza)
Description: A hot meal.

Name: Jones Memorial United Methodist Church
Description:
Full hot lunch the 2nd, 3rd &4th Wed of each month. Clothing &
toiletries available.

Name: Martin De Porres
Description: Dinning room serving at least one meal a day.
Hours: Sun Brunch 9-10:30am, Mon Breakfast 6:30am-7:30am, Tues Breakfast 6:30am-7:30am, Tues Lunch 12pm-2pm, Wed Lunch 12pm-2pm, Thurs Breakfast 6:30am-7:30am, Thurs Lunch12pm-2pm, Fri Breakfast 6:30am-7:30am, Fri Lunch 12pm-2pm, Sat Lunch 12pm-2pm
Notes: Usually a vegetarian or vegan alternative. Breakfast: oatmeal & herb tea. Brunch: a hearty meal. Lunch: a hearty soup & salad.

Name: North Peninsula Food Pantry & Dining Center of Daly City
Description: Dinner served three times a year.

Name: Providence Foundation of SF
Description: Hearty Lunch every Wednsday.
Notes: Optional Bible study before a hearty lunch.

Name: St. Peter & Paul Catholic Church
Description: A simple sandwhich offered everyday.

Name: S. F. Rescue Mission
Description: Breakfast and Dinner Monday through Friday.
Notes: Breakfast is coffee and pastry. Full course dinner is served at 3:45 pm. Blankets may be available. Mandatoory church service at 4pm. Doors close at 4:15pm.

Name: Third Baptist Church
Description: Hearty Lunch every Thursday
Notes: Meat, bread, vegetables, salad, punch, & dessert.

Name: United Council of Human Services
Description: Hot breakfast. Hot dinner.

Name: Calvary United Methodist Church
Description: Hot breakfast on the first & third Sunday of the month. Pancakes, grits, eggs.

Name: First Friendship Institutional Baptist Church
Description: Hot meal forth Saturday of the month.

Name: Iglesia Latina Americana de las Adventistas 7 Dia
Description: Lacto-ovo-vegitarian! Eggs, rice, beans, & cocoa or punch served on the  third Sunday of each month.

Name: Macedonia Missionary Baptist Church
Description: A full course meal the Saturday before the forth Sunday of each month.
Notes: There is a short blessing before the meal.

Name: Philadelphian 7th-Day Adventist Church
Description: Lacto-ovo-vegitarian! Fruit, cereal, juice, bread, milk, entree & hot beverage on the second & forth Sundays of the month.
